<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Iceberg, dead ahead!</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Warsword Keenblade">Warsword Keenblade</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:27 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Iceberg, dead ahead!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=466" TARGET=_self>Iceberg, dead ahead!</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>By "making PvP work in Everquest I assume that you mean within the PvP community. In that regard you have my wholehearted support.

<P>I must admit that I have not yet tried a +PvP character although I hope to remedy this oversight during phase 4. Perhaps this will give me a greater insight into the problems of +PvP on EQ. We'll see.
<P>For now however I am somewhat paranoid that if opened to randon PvP EQ will end up like UO, a game I and my whole family left due to the rampant ujncontrolle dominance of PKing and exploiters.
<P>Phase 4 will be interesting in that here we should see what the effect of a predictable influx of "KewlDoodZ" is going to do to "our" game.
<P>I hope EQ is able to resist this onslaught just as much as I hope that you who wish to engage in +PvP get the balance and ability to pursue your avocation that you desire, within your ranks and to as much enjoyment as we mainly -PvPs have found in ours.
<P>Good Travels Brother!
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
